 with it intolerance of ethnic, sexual, and all other minority groups, and a rejection of democratic society. We Resist gathers the compelling perspectives of scholars and activists who are deeply embedded within political and community struggles, who participate in policy decisions, and who are engaged in research that advances those struggles. An essential and timely book, We Resist confronts the problems we face as a human community and impels a cross-sectoral movement to defend our rights and revitalize the common good.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCommon good. 0aSocial action. 0aSocial problems. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Advocacy.2bisacsh1 aArmstrong, Pat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBehrens, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoudry, Aziz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorrigan, Edward C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDay, Richard J.F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD’Arcy, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEgan, Carolyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElghawaby, Amira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarber, Bernie M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraham, Melissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaiven, Max, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenaway, Mostafa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHogben, Alia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/v